    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4646739358\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Great idea! A handful of comments below</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608756188,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783440184
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3537833774\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Can we define a <code>ShardId</code> newtype? And then have helpers on each pool type to go from <code>ShardId</code> to its sharded pool.</p>\n<p>This would also let <code>ShardId</code> be represented as a <code>u32</code>, which should make some of the data structures here quite a bit more compact (eg the <code>per_shard</code> in <code>free_many</code>).</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608756192,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783440185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3537813454\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This logic to distribute slots across shards is a little subtle, especially in the face of a pool whose capacity doesn't evenly divide by the shard size. Could we have a <code>proptest</code> or <code>mutatis::check</code> test that asserts that summing up each shards slots and max unused warm slots gives us the expected total? Might want to factor out some pure logic while doing this so that the <code>available_parallelism</code> call becomes a parameter and the property test isn't checking only the host's hardware configuration.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608756194,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783440185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3537847531\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This logic seems to be repeated a few times as well, could we wrap it up in a helper?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608756196,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783440185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3537899413\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Should <code>flush_all_decommit_queues</code> instead be something like <code>flush_next_decommit_queue</code> where it returns <code>true</code> as soon as any sharded queue's decommit returned a slot to the pool, rather than eagerly flushing all slots? This would avoid a number of lock acquisitions (at the cost of raising the chances that someone else steals the flushed slots before we get a chance to grab it). A good balance might be something like this:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">None</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"fm\">assert!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decommit_queues</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decommit_queues</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">flush_next_decommit_queue</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"k\">continue</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608756199,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783440185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3537821082\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>FWIW, I'm imagining something similar to our existing property test here: <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/6918520e213c1cce4c4f790907d2f9482056e3ed/crates/wasmtime/src/runtime/vm/instance/allocator/pooling/memory_pool.rs#L1015\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/6918520e213c1cce4c4f790907d2f9482056e3ed/crates/wasmtime/src/runtime/vm/instance/allocator/pooling/memory_pool.rs#L1015</a></p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608756200,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783440185
    },
