    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3538809877\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Agreed yeah, and I wasn't too comfortable with the subtlety here either. I hadn't thought of using a proptest though, which I think is a great idea.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608811671,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783449298
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> tschneidereit submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4647965861\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 608812873,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783449733
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3538849531\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Good call, yeah, and that's roughly what I implemented now. We could alternatively introduce something like <code>free_many_and_alloc_one</code> which would remove the risk of the slot being stolen. I'd like to at least do that in another PR though, given that the issue is preexisting, to the degree it's a real concern.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608812875,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783449733
    },
