    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4655268913\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 609013338,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523786
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3544952860\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Could this method be deleted and tests updated to call <code>deallocate_many</code>?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013342,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523786
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3544958372\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Did you see much benefit from using this? I'd naively expect this to be a bit too low level of a micro-optimization for us to see much benefit in the pooling allocator, but I'm also not entirely sure.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013343,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523786
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3544963027\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>FWIW if you drop the <code>const</code> this'll get evaluated at first-use meaning that the initialiation below with a <code>fetch_add</code> can be placed here directly and then it can be accessed as-is.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013344,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523786
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3544992138\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Can this update the documentation of <code>decommit_batch_size</code> in <code>config.rs</code> to indicate that the queued-to-be-released can actually be up to <code>16 * (batch_size - 1)</code> as opposed to <code>batch_size - 1</code>?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013345,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523786
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545006595\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I realize this is preexisting, but one possible improvement here would be to drop the <code>queue</code> lock before the closure <code>f()</code> is called to minimize the scope of the critical section here. Same for memory/table allocation below, too.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013347,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523786
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545030611\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think this allocation is one reason CI is failing, notably this isn't handling OOM. We've got <code>try_collect</code> helpers though which can then be used to handle this</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013348,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523786
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545081516\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Huh well ok given that preexisting this was <code>.collect()</code> maybe I'm totally off about what's causing the failure in fuzzing....</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013349,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523786
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545052095\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This <code>.collect()</code> I think may also need to become <code>try_collect</code> to handle OOM</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013350,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523787
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545038671\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think this is failing on miri since this reads the local current directory, but feel free to put <code>#[cfg_attr(miri, ignore)]</code> on these proptest tests</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013351,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523787
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545100277\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This I think is the same as <code>decommit_shard_ids</code> in the main pooling allocator, could there perhaps be a helper that returns an <code>impl Iterator</code> of shard ids starting with the current thread's home and wraps around?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013352,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523787
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545154949\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A few thoughts on this: primarily could this be deduplicated with the above method? We've gotten ids/shards/etc wrong here in the past so it's subtle enough I'd prefer not to duplicate.</p>\n<p>Otherwise though, could/should this use a <code>SmallVec</code> in the same manner as the index allocator? Looking at this again, too, this might be where the OOM tests are failing (OOM on the <code>push</code> here). We don't have an OOM-handling version of <code>SmallVec</code>, however, meaning that switching to <code>SmallVec</code> would perhaps paper over the OOM happening without actually addressing it, but that could be handled in a follow-up</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609013353,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783523787
    },
