    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545554839\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Done.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609027318,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527208
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> tschneidereit submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4655979718\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 609027377,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527222
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545556234\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I didn't A/B this specifically, so I can't claim a measured win for it. The rationale: the shards are stored inline in the <code>Box&lt;[_]&gt;</code>, so without padding the tail of one shard's <code>Inner</code>/<code>DecommitQueue</code> (frequently-written fields) can end up on the same cache line as the next shard's mutex word. The cost is bounded (≤16 shards × ≤128 bytes of padding per pool), so I kept it as cheap insurance — but happy to drop it if you'd rather not carry it without a measurement.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609027379,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527222
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> tschneidereit submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4655979870\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 609027380,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527222
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545556383\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>That's actually already the case, though it's easy to miss: <code>flush_decommit_queue</code> takes the queue out of the mutex and drops the guard <em>before</em> doing the actual decommit, so neither the flush nor the retry of <code>f()</code> (nor the memory/table allocation retries below) runs while a queue lock is held. I extended the doc comment on <code>with_flush_and_retry</code> to make that explicit.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609027383,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527223
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> tschneidereit submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4655981627\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 609027447,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527239
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545558113\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Done — this now uses <code>try_collect</code>, and the index-allocator constructors are fallible as well. FWIW, the abort in the OOM tests turned out to be <code>pooling_allocator_fiber_stack_slot_leak_on_oom</code> hitting the intermediate <code>Vec</code> that <code>StackPool::deallocate_many</code> / <code>TablePool::deallocate_many</code> built on the deallocation path; those now feed their iterator straight into <code>free_many</code> instead. The <code>--cfg arc_try_new</code> OOM suite aborted before these changes and passes with them (188/188 locally).</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609027449,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527239
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> tschneidereit submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4655981775\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 609027452,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527240
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545558265\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Done — <code>ShardLayout::new</code> and the allocator constructors now return <code>Result&lt;_, OutOfMemory&gt;</code> and use <code>try_collect</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609027455,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527240
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> tschneidereit submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4655981921\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 609027462,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527241
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545558420\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The two fuzz-test failures in the queue run (<code>smoke_test_memory_access</code> and <code>gc_ops_eventually_gcs</code>) do look unrelated to this PR: they failed on the GC heap's minimum size exceeding the configured memory limit, i.e. an interaction with the state main was in during that merge-queue batch (#13841 was in flight at the time). Both tests pass locally on this branch merged with current main. The OOM-test abort was real, though — see the other thread.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609027465,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527242
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> tschneidereit submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4655982093\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 609027473,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527243
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545558595\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Done — added a <code>shard_ids_from_home</code> helper in <a href=\"http://pooling.rs\">pooling.rs</a>, used by both the decommit-queue paths and the index allocator's <code>alloc</code> probing.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609027477,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527243
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> tschneidereit submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#pullrequestreview-4655982229\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 609027487,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527244
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> tschneidereit created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13840#discussion_r3545558735\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Done on both counts: the subtle slot/stripe translation now lives in a shared <code>return_slot</code> helper used by both methods, and <code>deallocate_many</code> batches per-stripe frees in <code>SmallVec</code>s of the same shape as the index allocator's <code>free_many</code>. The OOM-on-spill caveat applies as you say and would be for a follow-up — the abort the OOM tests actually hit was the stack/table pools' intermediate <code>Vec</code>s, which are now gone entirely.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609027490,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783527244
